# 🔍 Linux Log Analysis — SOC Investigation

## Objective
Kali Linux pe real log analysis ki jaise 
ek SOC Analyst karta hai

## Environment
- OS: Kali Linux (VMware)
- Date: March 2026

## Tools Used
- journalctl
- lastb / last / lastlog
- netstat / ss
- grep, awk, cut

## Investigation Steps

### 1. Log Files Structure Dekhi
/var/log/ directory mein available logs:
- apache2/ — Web server logs
- auth.log — Authentication logs  
- dpkg.log — Package installation logs
- journal/ — Systemd logs
- btmp/wtmp — Login history

### 2. System Errors Analysis
Command: journalctl -p err -n 20 --no-pager

Findings:
| Error | Cause | Severity |
|-------|-------|----------|
| SMBus Host Controller | VMware virtual hardware | ✅ Normal |
| Bluetooth hci0 failed | No BT in VM | ✅ Normal |
| GDM Keyring warning | GNOME login issue | ⚠️ Low |
| Network timeout | Boot time delay | ⚠️ Monitor |

### 3. Login Activity Check
Command: lastb (failed) / last (successful)
Result: No suspicious brute force detected ✅

### 4. Network Connections
Command: netstat -tulnp
Result: Normal system ports only ✅

## SOC Conclusion
```
🟢 SYSTEM STATUS: CLEAN
No malware, no brute force,
no suspicious activity detected!
```

